The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, March 24, 2004 				 Arif debut
																								Ahmedabad, March 23: Arif Mohammed Khan was disappointed on his first visit to Gujarat today since joining the BJP, and said so twice, reports our correspondent.																								He was disheartened by the poor turnout and the unfavourable response from his new party  not a single prominent BJP leader was present at a convention organised by the Fans of Arif Mohammed Khan. 																								But, putting on a brave face, the leader said he faced no moral dilemma in joining a party he had blamed for the 2002 Gujarat riots.																								Khan said: Democracy is not all about voting. It is also about creating alternatives and options for the people and by joining the BJP, I have created an alternative for you (Muslims). 
